      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Great choice with the rye flour! As for what to watch out for, a few things can indicate that your starter is on the right track. If it starts to bubble and the surface looks frothy, that's a good sign. You might also notice a pleasant, slightly sour smell, which is a good indicator that your yeast and bacteria are doing their job. As for the texture, it should become more bubbly and rise slightly when you mix it.\n\nIf you notice any off smells, like a strong ammonia smell, or if the texture becomes slimy or moldy, that's a sign that something might be off, and you should discard the starter and start fresh. But if it's just taking a bit longer to wake up, don't worry too much. Sometimes it just needs a little more time and patience. Keep feeding it regularly and give it a few more days. Your sourdough starter will soon be as lively as a mischievous goblin, ready to help you bake some delicious bread!",
